Cacique Restaurant is at the heart of Downtown, a rather popular place to eat.  We travel Downtown often during the year to attend Miami-Dade County Board of County Commissioner's meetings, or to go for Jury Duty.  We also travel Downtown to visit the Frost Museum of Science or go shopping, and we always go to this particular restaurant because the food is excellent, the staff very professional and friendly, and the owner makes us feels as if we are family.  Every time we eat here, we see County officials, attorneys, bailiffs, or employees of the shops that surround the establishment.  Prices are reasonable and they are prompt in service, making sure we are able to eat within the allotted time for most of the people that work around the restaurant.  If you go Downtown, try it and you shall become a regular. We are customers for life!
